I used the task &lt;java&gt; to execute the TestCases for ant with the same 
classpath 
example
======================================================
&lt;java
           fork        = &quot;yes&quot;
           classname   = &quot;junit.textui.TestRunner&quot;
           taskname    = &quot;JUnit&quot;
           failonerror = &quot;true&quot; &gt;

         &lt;arg value=&quot;test.foo.cle.TestAll&quot;/&gt; 
	&lt;classpath&gt;
        	 &lt;pathelement location=&quot;${TEST_CONTEXT_BUILD}&quot;/&gt;
        	 &lt;pathelement location=&quot;${JAVA_BUILD_DIR}&quot;/&gt;
================================================================
It works.. finds all the depended classes.

But when I switch to task Junit ..ant fails to find all the classes. 
example
=======================================
    &lt;target name=&quot;test_cle4&quot; depends=&quot;compile_cle,test_context&quot; 
description=&quot;Run all JUnit tests&quot;&gt;
     &lt;junit printsummary=&quot;no&quot; fork=&quot;no&quot; haltonfailure=&quot;no&quot;&gt;
	&lt;classpath&gt;
        	 &lt;pathelement location=&quot;${JAVA_BUILD_DIR}&quot;/&gt;
        	  &lt;pathelement location=&quot;${TEST_CONTEXT_BUILD}&quot;/&gt;
=====================================================

It finds some, not all. In my TestCases I could narrow it down to the 
classes loaded dynamically within the code.

But if I change the system classpath manually and then run the script 
it finds all classes.

It also does not find it if I update the systemclasspath from the 
script at run time.
example &lt;sysproperty key=&quot;CLASSPATH&quot; 
path=&quot;${TEST_CONTEXT_BUILD};${JAVA_BUILD_DIR}&quot;/&gt;

I feel the above problem is valid for third party libs used by the 
testcase. Move the libs to Ant_home.. and ant finds it else it finds 
some not all

Any suggestions

-Shaji


